The paper proposes a data-driven approach using deep Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for separating compound figures in scientific papers. This involves image processing and computer vision techniques, which are commonly associated with the computer science sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV), information retrieval (cs.IR), deep learning (cs.DL), natural language processing (cs.CL), and multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
